main event: A UFO was observed crossing the sky at very high speed, estimated at approximately 1350 MPH.
interesting points: The UFO was described as a blob of light with a very high speed and an estimated velocity of 1350 MPH.
There were no stars visible in the area as it descended.
The witness initially believed it to be a kite due to its small appearance, but then realized it was a UFO.
The UFO had the appearance of a floating white light, oval, and bright without any red lights like that of the moon on a clear night.
The witness could not remember the weather conditions, which suggests that the object could have been at a high altitude.
The UFO was tracked through binoculars and observed to have a straight flight course before disappearing.
The witness chose not to note the occurrence, thinking it unimportant, and later included it in their memoirs.
